< Bind by `working_dirs` using your project's absolute path. This sets **window affinity** — routing tool calls to the correct window without pinning a specific tab:
< 	`{"op":"bind","working_dirs":["/path/to/project"]}`
< Add `create_if_missing=true` to create and pin a new tab if no match exists.
---
> Bind by `working_dirs` using the exact absolute workspace root paths. Matching is against the full workspace `repo_paths` set, order-insensitive, not descendant paths:
> 	`{"op":"bind","working_dirs":["/path/to/root1","/path/to/root2"]}`
> If the matching workspace is already open, RepoPrompt prefers that window. If it exists but is not open, RepoPrompt opens a window and switches to it. Add `create_if_missing=true` to create a new workspace after approval when no exact match exists.
