< **Window/tab model:**
< - Binding by `working_dirs` or `context_id` auto-resolves across windows — no manual window selection needed
< - `bind_context.list` is the **per-window routing view** — shows windows with tabs and context_ids
< - `manage_workspaces.list` is the **workspace inventory view** — shows workspaces with folder paths
< - When the same workspace is open in multiple windows, compose tabs are shared logical state
---
> **Binding modes:**
> - **Window affinity** (from working_dirs or window_id): routes tool calls to whichever tab is currently active in that window. Most agents should use this.
> - **Tab binding** (from context_id): pins tool calls to a specific compose tab, even if you switch to another tab. Use when you need a stable context that won't change.
214a212,215
> **Discovery:**
> - Use `bind_context list` to see what's currently open (windows, active workspaces, tabs, context_ids)
> - Use `manage_workspaces list` to see all saved workspaces, including ones not currently open
> 
